text: hi everyone
crowthanymagtano here the internet's

caveworld this is the third full-length
lp of sweden's own viagra boys within a
matter of several years these guys have
become one of the best and most
enjoyable most fantastic most fun and
interesting post punk bands on the scene
but they did not gain their success at
least in my opinion by being merely an
exercise in nostalgia just merely
holding to the genres more traditional
forms as their grime cake productions
sleazy lyrics and absurd sense of humor
not only are pretty refreshing for this
style but feel very specific to them and
it's great to hear on this new lp not
only is all of that stuff carrying over
into this new batch of songs but on this
thing we're also getting an expanded
instrumental palette as well as some
pretty conceptual lyrical themes with a
lot of songs in the track list here
focusing on the dysfunction of the human
condition which of course is presented
in the frame of the modern day with all
of the paranoia and hatred and
conspiracy theories that are spread
across social media these days but
that's also juxtaposed against this
image of humanity as apes rudimentary
life forms that were destined for the
tragedy that we're currently in due to
our origins which plays out on tracks
like the cognitive tradeoff hypothesis
which sees front man sebastian murphy
ghoulishly theorizing about how we were
kicked out of the trees like in the
early days left to fend for ourselves
and had to essentially develop other
traits in order to survive there's even
a point where he questions whether or
not this change in evolution and
cognition has anything to do with his uh

the

how tight and
